{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Sentiment Analysis — Method Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "Benchmarks three approaches on the same dataset and compares accuracy, speed, and agreement.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Method | Module | Type |\n",
    "|--------|--------|------|\n",
    "| WordNet / SentiWordNet | `wordnet/` | Lexicon-based |\n",
    "| SenticNet | `senticnett/` | Knowledge-graph |\n",
    "| RoBERTa | `rober/` | Transformer |\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Before running:** make sure you have installed all dependencies and downloaded NLTK data.  \n",
    "> See `README.md` for setup instructions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 1. Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "import time\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Allow imports from project root (one level up from notebooks/)\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, '..')\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    classification_report,\n",
    "    confusion_matrix,\n",
    "    ConfusionMatrixDisplay,\n",
    "    accuracy_score,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "from wordnet.analyzer    import WordNetAnalyzer\n",
    "from senticnett.analyzer import SenticNetAnalyzer\n",
    "from rober.analyzer      import RoBERTaAnalyzer\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', palette='muted')\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.max_colwidth', 80)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('✓ Setup complete.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 2. Load dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "Place your CSV file in the `data/` folder.  \n",
    "Required columns: **`text`** (string) and **`label`** (`positive` / `negative` / `neutral`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Change this path to your own dataset if needed ──────────────────────────\n",
    "DATA_PATH = '../data/sample_reviews.csv'\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(DATA_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Validate columns\n",
    "assert 'text' in df.columns,  \"CSV must have a 'text' column\"\n",
    "assert 'label' in df.columns, \"CSV must have a 'label' column (positive/negative/neutral)\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Normalise labels to lowercase\n",
    "df['label'] = df['label'].str.lower().str.strip()\n",
    "df['text']  = df['text'].astype(str).str.strip()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Loaded {len(df):,} rows from: {DATA_PATH}')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('Label distribution:')\n",
    "print(df['label'].value_counts().to_string())\n",
    "print()\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 3. Initialise analyzers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "analyzers = {\n",
    "    'WordNet':   WordNetAnalyzer(),\n",
    "    'SenticNet': SenticNetAnalyzer(),\n",
    "    'RoBERTa':   RoBERTaAnalyzer(),   # model downloads ~500MB on first run\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "texts = df['text'].tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('✓ All analyzers ready.')\n",
    "print(f'  Dataset: {len(texts):,} samples')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 4. Run predictions & measure speed"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "timings = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for name, analyzer in analyzers.items():\n",
    "    print(f'Running {name}...', end='  ', flush=True)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    t0 = time.perf_counter()\n",
    "    results = analyzer.predict_batch(texts)\n",
    "    elapsed = time.perf_counter() - t0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    timings[name] = elapsed\n",
    "    df[f'{name}_label'] = [r.label.lower() for r in results]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ms_per = elapsed / len(texts) * 1000\n",
    "    print(f'done in {elapsed:.2f}s  ({ms_per:.1f} ms/sample)')\n",
    "\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('Predictions added to dataframe:')\n",
    "df[['text', 'label'] + [f'{n}_label' for n in analyzers]].head(8)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 5. Accuracy & classification report"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(f\"{'Method':<12}  {'Accuracy':>8}\")\n",
    "print('-' * 24)\n",
    "for name in analyzers:\n",
    "    acc = accuracy_score(df['label'], df[f'{name}_label'])\n",
    "    print(f\"{name:<12}  {acc:>8.1%}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for name in analyzers:\n",
    "    print(f'\\n{'=' * 40}')\n",
    "    print(f'  {name}')\n",
    "    print('=' * 40)\n",
    "    print(classification_report(\n",
    "        df['label'],\n",
    "        df[f'{name}_label'],\n",
    "        zero_division=0\n",
    "    ))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 6. Confusion matrices"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "labels_sorted = sorted(df['label'].unique())\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 4))\n",
    "fig.suptitle('Confusion Matrices — all three methods', fontsize=13, y=1.02)\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax, name in zip(axes, analyzers):\n",
    "    cm = confusion_matrix(df['label'], df[f'{name}_label'], labels=labels_sorted)\n",
    "    disp = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix=cm, display_labels=labels_sorted)\n",
    "    disp.plot(ax=ax, colorbar=False, cmap='Blues')\n",
    "    acc = accuracy_score(df['label'], df[f'{name}_label'])\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'{name}\\n(acc {acc:.1%})', fontsize=11)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('confusion_matrices.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "print('Saved: confusion_matrices.png')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 7. Speed comparison"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ms_per_sample = {k: v / len(texts) * 1000 for k, v in timings.items()}\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 3))\n",
    "colors = ['#5B8DCA', '#5BAB87', '#D47A5B']\n",
    "\n",
    "bars = ax.barh(\n",
    "    list(ms_per_sample.keys()),\n",
    "    list(ms_per_sample.values()),\n",
    "    color=colors,\n",
    "    height=0.5,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Value labels on bars\n",
    "for bar, val in zip(bars, ms_per_sample.values()):\n",
    "    ax.text(\n",
    "        val + max(ms_per_sample.values()) * 0.01,\n",
    "        bar.get_y() + bar.get_height() / 2,\n",
    "        f'{val:.1f} ms',\n",
    "        va='center',\n",
    "        fontsize=10,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Average time per sample (ms)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Inference speed comparison', fontsize=12)\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(0, max(ms_per_sample.values()) * 1.2)\n",
    "ax.invert_yaxis()\n",
    "sns.despine()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('speed_comparison.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "print('Saved: speed_comparison.png')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 8. Agreement analysis — where do the methods disagree?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "method_cols = [f'{n}_label' for n in analyzers]\n",
    "\n",
    "df['n_unique_labels'] = df[method_cols].nunique(axis=1)\n",
    "df['all_agree']       = df['n_unique_labels'] == 1\n",
    "df['majority_label']  = df[method_cols].mode(axis=1)[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Agreement summary\n",
    "agree_all  = df['all_agree'].sum()\n",
    "agree_two  = (df['n_unique_labels'] == 2).sum()\n",
    "agree_none = (df['n_unique_labels'] == 3).sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Agreement summary')\n",
    "print('-' * 35)\n",
    "print(f'All 3 agree:         {agree_all:4d}  ({agree_all/len(df):.1%})')\n",
    "print(f'2 of 3 agree:        {agree_two:4d}  ({agree_two/len(df):.1%})')\n",
    "print(f'All 3 disagree:      {agree_none:4d}  ({agree_none/len(df):.1%})')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Pairwise agreement\n",
    "names = list(analyzers.keys())\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('Pairwise agreement')\n",
    "print('-' * 35)\n",
    "for i in range(len(names)):\n",
    "    for j in range(i+1, len(names)):\n",
    "        a, b = names[i], names[j]\n",
    "        match = (df[f'{a}_label'] == df[f'{b}_label']).mean()\n",
    "        print(f'{a} vs {b}:  {match:.1%}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Samples where all three methods disagree — most interesting for analysis\n",
    "disagreements = df[df['n_unique_labels'] == 3].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "if len(disagreements) == 0:\n",
    "    print('No samples where all three methods disagreed.')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f'{len(disagreements)} samples where all three methods gave different labels:\\n')\n",
    "    display(\n",
    "        disagreements[['text', 'label'] + method_cols]\n",
    "        .reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "        .head(15)\n",
    "        .style.applymap(\n",
    "            lambda v: 'color: green' if v == 'positive'\n",
    "                      else ('color: red' if v == 'negative' else 'color: gray'),\n",
    "            subset=method_cols\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 9. Error analysis — what did each method get wrong?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for name in analyzers:\n",
    "    col = f'{name}_label'\n",
    "    errors = df[df['label'] != df[col]].copy()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f'\\n── {name} errors: {len(errors)} / {len(df)} ──────────────')\n",
    "    if len(errors) > 0:\n",
    "        # What was predicted vs actual?\n",
    "        error_summary = (\n",
    "            errors\n",
    "            .groupby(['label', col])\n",
    "            .size()\n",
    "            .reset_index(name='count')\n",
    "            .rename(columns={'label': 'true', col: 'predicted'})\n",
    "            .sort_values('count', ascending=False)\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        print(error_summary.to_string(index=False))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        print(f'\\nTop misclassified examples:')\n",
    "        display(errors[['text', 'label', col]].head(5).reset_index(drop=True))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 10. Summary"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('━' * 55)\n",
    "print(f\"{'Method':<12} {'Accuracy':>9} {'ms/sample':>10} {'Errors':>8}\")\n",
    "print('━' * 55)\n",
    "for name in analyzers:\n",
    "    acc    = accuracy_score(df['label'], df[f'{name}_label'])\n",
    "    ms     = timings[name] / len(texts) * 1000\n",
    "    errors = (df['label'] != df[f'{name}_label']).sum()\n",
    "    print(f\"{name:<12} {acc:>9.1%} {ms:>10.1f} {errors:>8}\")\n",
    "print('━' * 55)\n",
    "\n",
    "best_acc  = max(analyzers, key=lambda n: accuracy_score(df['label'], df[f'{n}_label']))\n",
    "best_spd  = min(analyzers, key=lambda n: timings[n])\n",
    "print(f'\\n  Best accuracy : {best_acc}')\n",
    "print(f'  Fastest       : {best_spd}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### When to use which method\n",
    "\n",
    "| Method | Use when |\n",
    "|--------|----------|\n",
    "| **WordNet** | You need speed, full offline use, or interpretability (you can see exactly why a score was given) |\n",
    "| **SenticNet** | Your text contains multi-word expressions or commonsense reasoning matters (e.g. "not bad") |\n",
    "| **RoBERTa** | Accuracy is the priority — especially for social media, informal text, sarcasm, or negation |"
   ]
  }
 ],
